A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a busy office workspace where an anthropomorphic owl wearing horn-rimmed glasses sits at a wooden desk, carefully observing a group of small mice workers going about their daily tasks at miniature workstations. The owl holds a leather-bound notebook and fountain pen, leaning forward with genuine curiosity. Scattered across the desk are colorful index cards, sticky notes on papers, and small artifacts the mice use in their work. The warm sepia and mustard color palette evokes mid-century modern design. Through a large window, a cityscape suggests a corporate setting. The composition emphasizes the contrast between distant observation and close, engaged watching—the owl positioned not above but beside the mice, at their level, creating a sense of collaborative discovery rather than surveillance.
